TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Value of Information in Competitive Markets: Evidence from Small and Medium-Sized Enterprises
AU  - Galdon-Sanchez, Jose Enrique
AU  - Gil, Ricard
AU  - Uriz-Uharte, Guillermo
Y1  - 2024/08/05
PY  - 2024
DA  - 2025/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/732525
DO  - 10.1086/732525
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 252
EP  - 305
VL  - 133
IS  - 1
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - We empirically investigate how the performance of small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) changes when gaining access to market information. To do so, we evaluate the impact of an information program diffused by a bank among its SME customers. Adopting firms gained access to reports with rich information about their own clientele and that of nearby establishments. While we find that adoption is associated with a 4.5% revenue increase, our instrumental variable results indicate that adoption increases revenue by 9%. The main mechanism driving our result is that the new information prompted adopting establishments to target gender-age customer groups underserved before adoption.
AB  - We empirically investigate how the performance of small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) changes when gaining access to market information. To do so, we evaluate the impact of an information program diffused by a bank among its SME customers. Adopting firms gained access to reports with rich information about their own clientele and that of nearby establishments. While we find that adoption is associated with a 4.5% revenue increase, our instrumental variable results indicate that adoption increases revenue by 9%. The main mechanism driving our result is that the new information prompted adopting establishments to target gender-age customer groups underserved before adoption.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/732525
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/732525
Y2  - 2025/02/26
